  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Is there a reason that transferOwnership() doesn't throw an error if the address is 0?  I think silently failing could cause users/contracts to think that the ownership transfer succeeded even though they messed something up.  This could lead to further problems.\r\n\r\n```\r\n  function transferOwnership(address newOwner) onlyOwner {\r\n    if (newOwner != address(0)) {\r\n      owner = newOwner;\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n```",
